"{\"uid\": \"salon.com-2024-08-07-rebeca-andrade-olympics-habit\", \"text\": \"Brazilian gymnast Rebeca Andrade and top Team USA opponent at the Paris Olympics shared a unique anecdote about one of the ways she prepares herself for competition. Andrade bested U.S. standoutSimone Bilesin thewomen's floor event,earning a score of 14.166 and the top podium position after claiming the silver medal in the women's all-around.  When asked this week what she does to pump herself up, Andrade shared that she tends to focus on food and television.\\u00c2\\u00a0\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI was thinking about the recipes that I will make when I get back to Brazil,\\\" she said,according to NPR.\\u00c2\\u00a0\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThere was one that was with potatoes and cheese, chicken. There\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s cake. There\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s cookies. A lot of things.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  When it came to what she did before her golden floor routine, Andrade that she had a certain medical drama series on her mind.\\u00c2\\u00a0\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cToday, I wasn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t thinking about recipes because I watched a lot of TV shows [episodes] yesterday,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Andrade after her win. \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cSo I dreamed of the show I was watching. I was watching:'Grey\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Anatomy.'So I dreamed that I was a doctor, that I was operating and so on.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d\\u00c2  Andrade had previously won a gold medal in the vault event at the Tokyo Games in 2021 after Biles withdrew from the competition after being plagued with a bout ofthe \\\"twisties.\\\"  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2026 Salon.com, LLC. Reproduction of material from any Salon pages without written permission is strictly prohibited. SALON \\u00c2\\u00ae is registered in the U.S. Patent and Trademark Office as a trademark of Salon.com, LLC. Associated Press articles: Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2016 The Associated Press. All rights reserved. This material may not be published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed.  DMCA Policy  By subscribing, you agree that Salon will automatically charge you at the then-current rate (currently $9.95/month or $95/year) each month/year until you cancel. Log in to your account anytime to cancel prior to renewal date and avoid future charges.  Your current signup type is\"}"